  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Assistive technology - Vision Aid</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to create an atmosphere whereby the Visually Impaired (VI) are provided with training for personal development, career enhancement, bring in a facilitative environment and to train teachers of the VI children so that they are able to provide this training to their students in schools. 

The programme focuses on providing computer skill training to the VIs from Vizag and the neighbouring sub districts. It also supports colleges for setting up satellite training centres where VIs students are enrolled through which VI students are trained in computers. Besides, it trains the teachers and the students pursuing Bachelors of Education (B. Ed) with an aim that these individuals will further use the learn skills while teaching VI students. Also a resource centre has been established under this project which has few computers that can be utilised by the students for practise and also has various devices for persons with blindness and Low Vision. This acts as a centre for creating awareness among the general public and also among those interested in working for people with VI.</narrative>
  </description>
